Comments on Codes:
"Highest-priority comment:
The app does not meet the user’s terminal-play requirement: main.py launches a Tkinter GUI and there is no CLI game loop that accepts moves like “Ke8” in the Linux terminal. Worse, importing tkinter at top-level will fail on headless servers even if the user only wants terminal play.

How to fix:
- Move all GUI code out of main.py into a new gui.py so terminal use has no tkinter dependency.
- Replace main.py with a CLI driver that:
  - Instantiates Board and loops until checkmate/stalemate.
  - Prints the board/state each turn.
  - Reads user input (SAN like Ke8 or coordinates like e2e4), uses engine.san.parse_user_input to resolve a legal Move, and applies it.
  - Announces check, checkmate, stalemate, and winner.

Suggested replacement for main.py:
```python
# main.py — Terminal entry point
from engine.board import Board
from engine.san import parse_user_input, generate_san_for_move

def print_status(board: Board):
    turn = "White" if board.white_to_move else "Black"
    status = f"{turn} to move"
    if board.in_check(board.white_to_move):
        status += " - Check"
    print(status)

def print_result(board: Board):
    if board.is_checkmate():
